    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a pottery style that developed in Euboea, most notably from the seventh century BCE onward. It is characterized by distinctive Orientalizing and Black-figure designs that show the influence of Corinthian and Boeotian models.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000035191/Richter, Handbook of Greek Art (1974)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a un estilo de cerámica que se desarrolló en Eubea, más notablemente desde el siglo séptimo a.C en adelante. Se caracteriza por distintivos diseños Orientalizantes y de figura negra que muestran la influencia de los modelos Corintios y de Beocios.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een aardewerkstijl die zich ontwikkelde op Euboea, vooral vanaf de 7de eeuw v.Chr. Deze stijl wordt gekenmerkt door opvallende oriëntaliserende en zwartfigurige ontwerpen die Corinthische en Boeëtische invloeden verraden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱在尤比亞(Euboea)所發展的一種陶器風格，尤其是自西元前7世紀開始製作的陶器。此風格的特徵是極具特色的東方化手法與黑繪式設計圖案，展現出柯林斯風格與波也奧西亞風格的作品原型所帶來的影響。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
